author: Yogesh Narayan Swamy
text: From where I see...there s a lot to gain if we could find a way to work with China in global level...

reply.author: yashi kumar
reply.text: Yeah true

reply.author: bharat porwal
reply.text:
Yeah true!!
Infact i was also thinking the same But
Again when i was thiking about that, i pointed out some some issues in the indo-cino relations : 
1. Assertiveness of china - China is apspiring to be a leader in Asia and the only power which can held it, in present situation is India (though Japan is also there but not much strong).
2. Expansionist Policies of China- for example we can take example of south china sea.  Who so ever try to cooperate with china resulted in the shot in the arm.

3. India's own sovereign interests - cooperating with china till threshold means loosening the position of  India in case of POK, Arunachal pradesh which china every now and then claim as it's own part.

4. The gigantic Trade deficit -  India has the highest trade deficit with china Among All her trade partners and cooperating with china in this case would only surmount the burden of trade deficit.
 
5. The unipolar Asia -  supporting china which is powerful than India means accepting the chinies hegemony in the region. Which in the long run would not serve india's intrest.

There are many more reasons i  personally identified that you've already heard in news as  china's increasing presence in Indian ocean region , china's string of pearl policy, Debt trap policy, and All weather friendship with pakistan(though it can help in reducing terror activity in the region but china itself doesn't want that) 

And one more point  India's past experiences were not good with China too and there is a lack of trust , china's constant veto in NSG, UNSC on india's bid. And there are international  geopolitical dynamics which restrain india.

So these issues accordingg to me the bone of contentions in Increasing Cooperation woth China.
